# ğŸ›œ setup_wifi_ap.py

**`setup_wifi_ap.py`** is a Python automation script for Ubuntu that configures your system as a **Wi-Fi Access Point (AP)** using an existing Wi-Fi adapter and an Ethernet uplink.

It automatically handles:

- âœ… `hostapd` setup (Wi-Fi network configuration)
- âœ… `dnsmasq` setup (DHCP + DNS for Wi-Fi clients)
- âœ… `iptables` NAT and packet forwarding
- âœ… Disabling NetworkManager (to avoid conflicts)
- âœ… DHCP client setup on the Ethernet uplink
- âœ… Auto-validation of config files and service status

---

## ğŸ§° Requirements

- Ubuntu 18.04+ (tested on 20.04â€“24.04)
- Root privileges (`sudo`)
- One Wi-Fi adapter (to act as AP)
- One Ethernet adapter (Internet uplink)
- Python 3.6+

The script will automatically install:
```bash
hostapd dnsmasq iptables dhclient
```

---

